body.name: Shark Technology 750 Watt Quiet 120mm Blue LED Fan Black ATX 12V 2.0 PSU with All Braided Sleeving Cables and PCIe Power Connector Gaming PC System Power Supply
body.stockDetail: Only 11 left in stock - order soon.
features: Upgrade Power Supply for Most Dell Mini Tower PC and Standard Desktop ATX Computer Systems.
Quiet Operation with Smart Fan feature. Quad Power Status LEDs turn off when power is turned off.
Supports AMD multi-core and Intel i3/i5/i7 based systems. Innovative 4+4pin 12V connector supports 4pin 12V or 8pin 12V motherboard.
Black optimized thermal casing design with smart 120mm cooling fan protected by black low air-drag round circular fan guard. Long cables to be used in mini or mid tower cases

Connectors Details: (1) 24pin Main Power Connector (1) 4+4 12V Power Connector (Supports 4pin 12V or 8pin 12V), (1) 6+2 PCI-E Power Connector (supports 6pin or 8pin PCIe graphic card), (4) SATA power connectors (on 2 separate line of cables for unrestricted reach), (3) Molex 4-pin Peripheral Power Connector (also on 2 separate line of cables), (1) Floppy Drive Power Connector
body.description: SHARK TECHNOLOGY 750W computer PSU has a typical efficiency rating of 70%. A manual shut-down rocker switch next to the AC power cord plug allows user to shut down the system manually without resort to unplugging the power cord. Four (4) blue LED illuminating the fan while providing visual power status looking in from the back of the system. Input: 100-127V AC or 200-240V AC - select-able by switch. Dimension: 150mm x 86mm x 156mm (the 156mm length is the side that extends inside the case when installed). Smart fan controller with on-board thermostat dynamically controls fan speed to ensure ultra quiet operation - virtually fanless quiet.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The power supply works great and runs quietly
reviews.reviewText: The power supply works great and runs quietly, in my opinion a good bargain if you need a power supply that's got some juice. The blue glow is wasted on my Antec III case. My only gripe is the cables are kind of short, so I recommend this P.S. for mid to small cases, the cables will not be long enough with a full tower.

reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars ... to build a friends pc cause it was a good price for a 750w PSU
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to build a friends pc cause it was a good price for a 750w PSU. Figured it would run A GTX 980 just fine but nope. Anytime the card start to stress a little bit the power supply just gives out and the PC turns off. Plug in my power supply form my own computer to test and no problem at all. Would not recommend this if you have a high end GPU.
